Enid Lorimer https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Enid_Lorimer 0 May Enid Bosworth Nunn OAM (27 November 1887 – 15 July 1982), known professionally as Enid Lorimer and also known by the pseudonym of Ellen Bosworth, was a British-born Australian film, stage actress and director, radio and television actress, writer, teacher and theosophist. She was married to Count Wentworth Zerffi. She attended Herbert Trees theatre in London and trained as a Shakespearean actress, she was a contemporary of Dame Sybil Thorndike and Lilian Braithwaite. Miss Lorimer was also involved in silent film production in Britain during World War 1, working with the likes of Dame Ellen Terry.
